I"Ï<p><a href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Summum_bonum">Summum bonum</a> is a Latin expression meaning the highest or ultimate good. It was introduced by the Roman philosopher Cicero to denote the fundamental principle on which some system of ethics is based ‚Äî that is, the aim of actions, which, if consistently pursued, will lead to the best possible life.</p>

<p>Western civilization (in particular, the Judeo-Christian tradition) is based on the notion that summum bonum can be achieved by following the example of Israel. Israel is the name of the original Christian nation and the word itself means ‚Äú<a href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Jacob_wrestling_with_the_angel">wrestling with God</a>.‚Äù This wrestling match ‚Äì which pairs human reason with divine revelation ‚Äì is the subject and substance of this blog.</p>

